[10/14 20:05:35      3s] 	Prefix for the .log, .cmd, and .logv files. If it has an extension,
[10/14 20:05:35      3s] 	only the prefix is used. For example, either '-log abc' or '-log abc.log'
[10/14 20:05:35      3s] 	will create abc.log abc.cmd and abc.logv files. If the .log file already
[10/14 20:05:35      3s] 	exists, an integer is appended to all the file names to make them unique
